h3. Issue Summary
When adding a "Regular Expression Check" validator in the workflow and having the user default language set to Spanish can't be configured completely. 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Go to *Personal settings* (profile picture > Settings);
 # Set the *Language* to *español (España)*
 # Create a workflow;
 # Choose one transition and select *Validaciones*;
 # On the next screen select *Añadir validator*;
 # Select *Comprobación de expresiones regulares*;
 # Click on *Añadir*;

h3. Expected Results
The screen to configure the expression check will be presented;

h3. Actual Results
No configuration screen appears.

h3. Video
https://cl.ly/2f4d89c8f094

h3. Workaround
Configured the validator using the language set to English.

h3. Problem Statement

Curly Brackets "\{ }" is displayed on the New Issue View after importing from Jira backups
h3. Steps to replicate
 # Create a new issue on Cloud/Server instance
 # Using the *Old Issue View*, bold a sentence using curly brackets on Description/Comment field
eg.
{code:java}
{*}text here\{*}
{code}
 # Export Jira
 # Restore using the backup
 # View the same issue using New Issue View

h3. Expected result

*Curly Brackets hidden* from the New Issue View and text is bold
{panel}
 *text here*
{panel}

h3. Actual Result

*Curly Brackets is shown* from the New Issue View while text is bold out
{panel}
{}*text here*{}
{panel}

h3. Notes
 - Updating DB to remove curly braces (even to any other words) will update the old issue view *but not on the new issue view* using the query below:
{code:java}
Update jiraissue
set DESCRIPTION = REPLACE(DESCRIPTION,'\{*}','*')
where pkey = 'KAN' and issuenum = '8'
{code}

h3.  Workaround
View issues within the *old issue view*

h3. Issue Summary
When using the *Export Excel CSV (all fields)*  for sub-tasks of next-gen projects, the export fails and throws an error.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a next-gen project;
 # Create an issue;
 # Create a sub-task within that issue;
 # Go to the issue navigator and search for that issue;
 # Select the "Export Excel CSV (all fields)" option to export;

h3. Expected Results
A CSV file will be generated.

h3. Actual Results
No CSV is generated.
Video reproducing this behavior: https://cl.ly/85e446e7c0f9

h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Summary 
As an administrator I would like to have a REST API endpoint that I can call in order to export users to CSV. The same CSV export you can get from the instance user management when you click on 'export all users' documented in the below page:
- https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/export-users-from-a-site-833925313.html

h3. Workaround
It is possible to grab the cookie from an active site-admin session from the browser and then use it to authenticate a REST API POST request sent to the below internal endpoint (replace <CLOUD-ID> with your real cloud instance id):
{noformat}
https://admin.atlassian.com/gateway/api/adminhub/um/site/<CLOUD-ID>/users/export
{noformat}

As the body you can send something like:
{noformat}
{
includeApplicationAccess: true
includeGroups: false
includeInactiveUsers: true
selectedGroupIds: []
}
{noformat}

Please notice this is just a workaround, the endpoint is not official, not documented and may change over time. You may find a sample Python script in [this link|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-72942?focusedCommentId=2548077&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2548077].

h3. Summary

Currently, in the new issue view if the attachment name is lengthly and exceeded the width of the thumbnail. The name often displayed in a shorter format such as:

{qute}
20190909_Testing_File_On_New_Issue_View.csv 
{quote}

When you attached the file on new issue view the file name would be displayed as:

{quote}
20190909_Testing_Fil...View.csv{quote}
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 
It would be beneficial if we can adjust the name from the attachment thumbnails itself.

When you copy and paste a Confluence table into an issue comment it won't be displayed correctly in the comment.
h3. Steps to reproduce
 # Create a Confluence table (and enable "Numbered column");
 # Copy the entire table or just some lines;
 # Paste it into a comment (using the new issue view) and Save;
 # Observe that an empty comment is added to the issue;
 # Refresh the page and edit the empty comment
 # Observe the error below
{quote}*We can't display part of this content correctly*
 It contains formatting we don’t recognize. Before you save, test any links and check other content for formatting problems.
{quote}

!print.png|thumbnail!

h3. Workaround

If you clear the comment box when the error appears and paste the table again, the comment will be submitted correctly.

[Click here|https://cl.ly/0e27fcae168c] to see a video of this behavior.
